{
  "texts": [
    "It is worth noting that there is precedence for innovative technologies to stimulate the reimagination of policies, regulations, and enforcement approaches (Friedman 2001; Picker 2001).",
    "This dynamic represents a disruptive moment where practices and systems are destabilized (Liu et al. 2020).",
    "As a result, technological innovations can stimulate normative transformations (Friedman 2016; Picker 2001).",
    "This includes the capacity to confront and re-construct values, norms, ethical principles and practices that are entrenched (Danaher and Saetra 2023; Hopster and Maas 2023).",
    "It is suggested that this can occur through the re-shaping of decisions by the expansion of choice architecture, which in turn alters relational practices including power structures (Danaher and Saetra 2023)."
  ]
}